Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the routing and management of small unmanned aircraft systems (sUAS) in a high density urban area, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper also considers communication resource utilization as a constraint in the routing algorithm, indicating a networking and internet architecture aspect. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a temporal and spatial routing algorithm for sUAS trajectory management, which involves control and optimization of the system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence as it proposes an algorithm for sUAS routing and management. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper briefly mentions the need to consider airspace safety in the routing algorithm, which may involve security and cryptography aspects.
